    "text": "Not broken — 91% fits a strong rebound on paper. Ranked by contribution: you slept 8.2 h, about 0.4 h over your 7.8 h need; your HRV of 68 ms is about 8 ms above its 30-day baseline of 60 ms; and your resting heart rate of 53 bpm is about 3 bpm below its 30-day baseline of 56 bpm. A hard block followed by a big rebound often lines up with supercompensation, but that's an interpretation of the pattern, not a certainty. The practical read: today is a sensible one for your key quality session if it was already planned; the score says capacity is likely there, not that you must spend it.",
